// Strict (the default) rejects a spread whose source's static type
// is genuinely unknown. An untyped closure parameter leaks `Any`
// into the body scope, so the inner spread's source has no static
// type and strict demands a `<T>` hint.
// EXPECTED: 1 x SpreadSourceTypeUnknown (plus closure-param
// diagnostics for the untyped `n`).
{ f: (n) => { ...n } }
